<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><key>E</key>
<lyrics>[V1]
 Living below in this old sinful world,
 Hardly a comfort can afford;
 Striving alone to face temptations sore,
 Where could I go but to the Lord?

[C1]
   CHORUS
   Where could I go, O where could I go?
   Seeking a refuge for my soul?
   Needing a friend to help me in the end,
   Where could I go but to the Lord?

[V2]
 Neighbors are kind, I love them every
 one,
 We get along in sweet accord;
 But when my soul needs manna from
 above,
 Where could I go but to the Lord?

[V3]
 Life here is grand with friends I love so
 dear,
 Comfort I get from God's own word;
 Yet when I face the chilling hand of
 death,
 Where could I go but to the Lord?</lyrics>
<title>Where could I go?</title>
<presentation>v1 v2 v3 v4 </presentation>
</song>